'''煎餅帽'''（[[科瓦語|科瓦語]]：پکول‎，{{lang-ps|پکول}}，{{lang-fa|پکول}}，[[巴尔蒂语|巴尔蒂语]]：بروقپی نتینگ）<ref>{{cite web |title=My Cap, My Identity: Men's caps from Gilgit-Baltistan |url=https://pamirtimes.net/2016/10/01/my-cap-my-identity-mens-caps-from-gilgit-baltistan/ |website=Pamir Times |date=1 October 2016 |first=Ziab R |last=Mir |access-date=2020-07-27 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017225449/https://pamirtimes.net/2016/10/01/my-cap-my-identity-mens-caps-from-gilgit-baltistan/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first1=William|last1=Blackwood|title=Blackwood's Magazine | volume=303|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Ws4CAAAAMAAJ&q=gilgiti+cap&dq=gilgiti+cap|year= 1968}}</ref>又名'''奇特拉里帽'''<ref>{{cite book |first1=Amar Singh | last1=Chohan |title=A History of Kafferistan: Socio-economic and Political Conditions of the Kaffers |date=2014-07-14 }}</ref>，是一種圓形平頂，男性佩戴的軟式[[帽子|帽子]]，典型的煎餅帽使用[[羊毛|羊毛]]製成，它的外觀大多樸素，主要的顏色多為：褐色、黑色、灰色、象牙色或使用染料染成紅色。煎餅帽的帽名最早源自[[科瓦語|科瓦語]]，其在科瓦語中的名稱為'''科波爾帽'''，原意即是帽子<ref>{{Cite book|last=Condra|first=Jill|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=lazWAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA572&dq=Pakol+Khapol&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi5v8Sw3eDnAhUQ1xoKHQ5FD0gQ6AEIJzAA#v=onepage&q=Pakol%20Khapol&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of National Dress: Traditional Clothing around the World [2 volumes]|date=2013-04-09|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-37637-5|language=en|access-date=2020-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727131039/https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=lazWAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA572&dq=Pakol+Khapol&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi5v8Sw3eDnAhUQ1xoKHQ5FD0gQ6AEIJzAA#v=onepage&q=Pakol%20Khapol&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

有關於煎餅帽的起源尚有爭議，部分理論主張帽子可能發源自東南歐古馬其頓人的[[考西亞帽|考西亞帽]]，但大部分的歷史學家和民族學家在研究後取得共識，認為煎餅帽應當起源於[[奇特拉爾|奇特拉爾]]一帶<ref name="afghanistan-analysts1">{{cite web|url=https://www.afghanistan-analysts.org/from-alexander-the-great-to-ahmad-shah-massoud-a-social-history-of-the-pakol/|title=From Alexander the Great to Ahmad Shah Massoud: A Social History of the Pakol {{!}} Afghanistan Analysts Network|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-20|archive-date=2020-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201205059/https://www.afghanistan-analysts.org/from-alexander-the-great-to-ahmad-shah-massoud-a-social-history-of-the-pakol/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="google2000">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=CAUSAQAAIAAJ&q=pakol+peculiar&dq=pakol+peculiar&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj2mffe4ODnAhVSilwKHRdxBuMQ6AEIJTAA|title=Soldier of Fortune|date=2000|publisher=Omega Group, Limited|language=en|access-date=2020-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727090730/https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=CAUSAQAAIAAJ&q=pakol+peculiar&dq=pakol+peculiar&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj2mffe4ODnAhVSilwKHRdxBuMQ6AEIJTAA|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Chico|first=Beverly|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=GdbYAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA367&dq=pakol+origins&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjD7qjT2-DnAhVUT8AKHfKjA5sQ6AEIJTAA#v=onepage&q=pakol%20origins&f=false|title=Hats and Headwear around the World: A Cultural Encyclopedia: A Cultural Encyclopedia|date=2013-10-03|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-61069-063-8|language=en|access-date=2020-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727031245/https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=GdbYAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA367&dq=pakol+origins&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjD7qjT2-DnAhVUT8AKHfKjA5sQ6AEIJTAA#v=onepage&q=pakol%20origins&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。數世紀以來，羊毛製成的帽子一直是當地居民[[奇特拉爾人|奇特拉爾人]]主要配戴的服飾<ref>{{Cite book|last=Organisation (Pakistan)|first=Population Census|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=MzSFAAAAIAAJ&q=chitrali+cap&dq=chitrali+cap&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiI1-aR5eDnAhUzQUEAHfaTCH04ChDoAQgkMAA|title=1998 District Census Report of [name of District].: Chitral|date=1999|publisher=Population Census Organisation, Statistics Division, Govt. of Pakistan|language=en|access-date=2020-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727031105/https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=MzSFAAAAIAAJ&q=chitrali+cap&dq=chitrali+cap&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiI1-aR5eDnAhUzQUEAHfaTCH04ChDoAQgkMAA|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref> Swift, Hugh (1990). Trekking in Pakistan and India. Sierra Club Books. ISBN 978-0-87156-662-1. pakol tudor styled.</ref>。煎餅帽的生產以[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]的奇特拉爾地區為大宗<ref> Pushtun clothes choice-cold-nights/ "Pakol cap of Chitral"</ref>，而在[[吉尔吉特-巴尔蒂斯坦|吉尔吉特-巴尔蒂斯坦]]或[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]也普遍可見[[塔吉克族|塔吉克族]]、[[努里斯坦人|努里斯坦人]]或[[普什圖人|普什圖人]]等不同民族的男性配戴，[[努里斯坦省|努里斯坦省]]為奇特拉爾煎餅帽外銷的主要進口地區<ref>{{Cite book|last=Dupree|first=Louis|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=yvr_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA240&dq=chitrali+cap&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjpqLO44uDnAhUUXMAKHaVIAEwQ6AEIJTAA#v=onepage&q=chitrali%20cap&f=false|title=Afghanistan|date=2014-07-14|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-5891-0|language=en|access-date=2020-07-27|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727102717/https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=yvr_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA240&dq=chitrali+cap&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjpqLO44uDnAhUUXMAKHaVIAEwQ6AEIJTAA#v=onepage&q=chitrali%20cap&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

